quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  3,55,"Behold! Allah said: “O Iesa! Certainly I am the Giver of death to you and the Raiser of you towards Me and the Protector to you against those who rejected (you), and the Maintainer of those who have followed you above and higher to those who have rejected (you) — till the Day of Resurrection. Afterwards, towards Me is your returning place, then I will pronounce judgement between you people in whatever you used to create differences of opinion"
  3,56,"Then as to those who disbelieved, so I will punish them with a severe punishment in this world and the Hereafter; and not for them (is available anyone) from the helpers.”"
  3,57,"Then as to those who have Believed and have done righteous deeds, so He will pay them in full their rewards. And Allah does not like the transgressors"
  3,58,This (is what) We recite to you of the Verses and the Message full of wisdom
  3,59,"Certainly the similitude of Iesa before Allah is like the example of Adam. He created him from dust, then said to him: “Be\" — there he becomes"
  3,60,"Al-Haqq (coming) from your Nourisher-Sustainer, so be not of those who doubt"
  3,61,"Then whoever disputed with you concerning him after whatever has come to you from True knowledge, then say: “Come, we call our sons and your sons, our women and your women, our selves and your selves — then we pray to invoke, then we invite the curse of Allah upon those who lie.”"
  3,62,"Verily this! As usual it is the true narrative. And none is from (the category of) god except Allah. And indeed, Allah, certainly, He (is) All-Mighty, All-Wise"
  3,63,"So if they turned away, then surely, Allah (is) All-Aware of mischief mongers"